astro-ph/0511752 [abs, ps, pdf, other] :

          Title: Tidal Capture of Stars by Intermediate-Mass Black Holes
          Authors: H. Baumgardt, C. Hopman, S. Portegies Zwart, J. Makino
          Comments: 13 pages, 9 figures, submitted to MNRAS
          Recent  X-ray  observations and theoretical modelling have made
          it  plausible  that  some ultraluminous X-ray sources (ULX) are
          powered   by  intermediate-mass  black  holes  (IMBHs).  N-body
          simulations  have  also  shown that runaway merging of stars in
          dense  star  clusters  is  a  way to form IMBHs. In the present
          paper  we  have  performed N-body simulations of young clusters
          such  as  MGG-11  of  M82  in  which IMBHs form through runaway
          merging.  We  took  into account the effect of tidal heating of
          stars  by the IMBH to study the tidal capture and disruption of
          stars  by  IMBHs.  Our  results show that the IMBHs have a high
          chance  of  capturing  stars through tidal heating within a few
          core  relaxation times and we find that 1/3 of all runs contain
          a ULX within the age limits of MGG-11, a result consistent with
          the  fact  that  a  ULX  is  found  in this galaxy. Our results
          strengthen   the   case   for   some   ULX   being  powered  by
          intermediate-mass black holes.


  
