          order  to  get  detection  at  both wavelengths for most of the
          galaxies.  Star formation rate (SFR) estimators based on the UV
          and  FIR  emissions  are  compared.  Systematic differences are
          found  between the SFR estimators for individual galaxies based
          on  the  NUV  fluxes  corrected for dust attenuation and on the
          total  IR  luminosity. A combined estimator based on NUV and IR
          luminosities seems to be the best proxy over the whole range of
