          We  study  the mean environment of galaxies in the DEEP2 Galaxy
          Redshift  Survey as a function of rest-frame color, luminosity,
          and  [OII]  equivalent  width. The local galaxy overdensity for
          >14,000  galaxies  at  0.75  <  z < 1.35 is estimated using the
          projected  3rd-nearest-neighbor  surface density. Of the galaxy
          properties  studied,  mean  environment is found to depend most
