          is  a  scalar, $\beta_\mu$ is a four-vector, and $p^\mu$ is the
          four-momentum.   As   a   simple   example,  we  calculate  the
          relativistic  $\kappa$ power law for a dilute charged gas under
          the  action  of  an  electromagnetic  field  $F^{\mu\nu}$.  All
          standard  results  are readly recovered in the particular limit
