          galaxy  IC  342.  This  variable  source  has  an average X-ray
          luminosity of some 10^{40} erg/s. At the position of the source
          there is an ionized nebula (the "Tooth") having huge dimensions
          (280 x 130 pc), much larger than normal supernova remnants. Our
