          We  have  studied  the  dynamics  and masses of a sample of ten
          nearby  luminous and ultraluminous infrared galaxies (LIRGS and
          ULIRGs),  using  2.3 micron CO absorption line spectroscopy and
          near-infrared  H-  and  Ks-band  imaging. By combining velocity
          dispersions  derived  from the spectroscopy, disk scale-lengths
          obtained  from  the  imaging, and a set of likely model density
          profiles,  we calculate dynamical masses for each LIRG. For the
