          with  a  simple  power  law. The HeII/HI ratio eta is estimated
          using  a line profile-fitting procedure and an apparent optical
          depth   approach,   respectively.   The   expected  metal  line
          absorption  in  the  far-UV  is  taken  into account as well as
          molecular  absorption  of  galactic  H_2.  About 27% of the eta
          values  are  affected  by  metal  line  absorption. In order to
          investigate  the  applicability  of  the  analysis  methods, we
          create  simple  artificial  spectra  based  on  the statistical
          properties  of  the  HI  Ly  alpha  forest. The analysis of the
          artificial  data  demonstrates  that the apparent optical depth
          method  as  well  as the line profile-fitting procedure lead to
          confident  results for restricted data samples only (12.0 < log
          N(HI)  <  13.0).  The reasons are saturation in the case of the
          apparent  optical  depth and thermal line widths in the case of
          the  profile  fits.  Furthermore,  applying  the methods to the
          unrestricted  data  set may mimic a correlation between eta and
