          samples  a scatter of 10 - 15% in eta would be expected even if
          the  underlying  value  is  constant.  The  observed scatter is
          significantly   larger   than  expected,  indicating  that  the
          intergalactic  radiation  background  is indeed fluctuating. In
          the  redshift  range 2.58 < z < 2.72, where the data quality is
