          (5.8,  8  and  24 micron), of gamma~3. Comparison of the galaxy
          LFs  to  predictions  from  a  semi-analytic model based on CDM
          indicate  that an IMF skewed towards higher mass star formation
          in  bursts  compared  to  locally is preferred. As a result the
          currently  inferred  massive  star  formation  rates in distant
