          type  2  AGN)  are  unlikely to contribute significantly to the
          remaining  unresolved  hard  X-ray  background.  The red quasar
          population  includes objects with intrinsically red continua as
          well  as  objects  with dust-reddened continua. Improved sample
          selection  is  thus  needed  to  increase  our understanding of
          either  subpopulation. To identify dust-reddened quasars likely
          to exhibit X-ray absorption, some measure of spectral curvature
