          www.eso.org/~rsiebenm)  for  the  nuclei of starburst and ultra
          luminous  galaxies.  Its purpose is to quickly obtain estimates
          of  the  basic parameters, such as luminosity, size and dust or
          gas mass and to predict the flux at yet unobserved wavelengths.
          The  procedure  is simple and consists of finding an element in
          the  library  that matches the observations. The objects may be
          in the local universe or at high z.
