          field   spectroscopy   of  the  extended  emission-line  region
          associated  with quasar 3C 249.1. The complex global kinematics
          revealed  by the velocity field of the [O III] 5007 line cannot
          be  explained  by  a  simple  dynamical  model,  but  the local
          velocity  fields  of some distinct emission clouds appear to be
          consistent  with simple rotating disks. The temperatures of the
          ionized  gas  appear  uniform (varying from ~12000 to 15000 K),
