          nucleo-synthesized  much  of  the earth's carbon). The data are
          compared   to   structural   models   loosely  associated  with
          atom-by-atom,   molecule-by-molecule,   and   dendritic-droplet
          solidification processes. In this context the observed density,
          diffraction peak-shapes, and edge-on sheet patterns, along with
