          properties   of   a  typical  outburst  are  derived  from  the
          observations by decomposing the 19 lightcurves into a series of
          self-similar  events.  This analysis is achieved by fitting all
          data  simultaneously  to  a  succession  of  outbursts  defined
          according  to the shock-in-jet model of Marscher & Gear (1985).
