          3C273.  It  is argued that differences in the flaring behaviour
          of  these  two  sources are intrinsic to the sources themselves
          rather  than  being due to orientation effects. We also compare
          the  start  times  and flux densities of our modelled outbursts
          with  those  measured  from radio components identified in Very
          Long  Baseline  Interferometry  (VLBI)  images.  We  find  VLBI
          counterparts  for  most  of  our model outbursts, although some
          high-frequency  peaking  events are not seen in the radio maps.
          Finally,  we  study  the  link  between the appearance of a new
          synchrotron  component  and  the  EGRET  gamma-ray state of the
          source  at  10  different  epochs.  We find that an early-stage
