          Ia).   We   review   the   impact  of  this  mechanism  on  the
          luminosity-redshift  relation  of  SNe Ia, on the dispersion of
          quasar  spectra,  and  on  the spectrum of the cosmic microwave
          background.  The  original  idea  of  explaining  the  apparent
          dimming  of  distant  SNe  Ia  without  cosmic  acceleration is
          strongly  constrained  by  these arguments. However, the cosmic
          equation  of state extracted from the SN Ia luminosity-redshift
          relation  remains  sensitive to this mechanism. For example, it
          can mimic phantom energy.


   
