          distribution.   We  assume  a  uniform  UV  background  and  an
          isothermal  IGM  for  the  MHR00  model,  as  has  been done in
          previous  works.  Under  these  assumptions,  the  MHR00  model
          produces poor fits to the observed flux PDFs at redshifts where
          the  optical  depth  distribution is well sampled, unless large
          continuum  corrections  are  applied.  However,  the  lognormal
          optical  depth distribution fits the data at all redshifts with
          only   minor   continuum   adjustments.   We   use   a   simple
          parametrization  for  the evolution of the lognormal parameters
