          ergs/s,  the  power-law  photon  index softens to 2.5-3.0. This
          behavior is similar to the canonical spectral state transitions
          in  Galactic  black  hole binaries, but the source never enters
          the  high/soft or thermal dominant state and instead enters the
          steep  power-law  state  at  high  luminosities.  X-2  has  the
          opposite  behavior  and appears to be in the hard state, with a
          photon  index  of  Gamma=1.7-2.0  at  high  luminosity, but can
          soften to Gamma=2.5 at the lower luminosities.



