          contradict  the  predictions  for  the global mean interstellar
          metallicity  in galaxies from cosmic chemical evolution models,
          unless  selection effects are invoked. We investigate what role
          in  cosmic metal evolution is played by another important class
          of  quasar  absorbers, i.e. the sub-DLAs. We find that the mean
          Zn  metallicity of the observed sub-DLAs may evolve faster than
          that  of  the observed DLAs and reach a near-solar level at low
